# CLI & Template DNA Governance

## DNA generation flow

```
Source app (apps/tenant-*) --[npm run dist:dna:all]--> Template assets (packages/cli/assets/templates/<name>/)
```

Do NOT edit template DNA files directly. Always modify the source app first, then regenerate.

## Template structure

Each template in `packages/cli/assets/templates/<name>/` requires:

- `manifest.json` — template metadata (name, description, version)
- `src_tenant.sh` — deterministic shell script that emits tenant source files via heredocs

Legacy compatibility path for alpha: `packages/cli/assets/src_tenant_alpha.sh`

## CLI scaffolding flow

1. `npm create vite` — base Vite project
2. Overwrite `package.json`, `tsconfig.json`, `components.json` with template defaults
3. Execute `src_tenant.sh` — emits full `src/` directory (components, data, lib, config)

## Validation

- `npm run check:templates` — validates template presence and manifest consistency
- Run after any change to source apps or template assets

## Adding a new template

1. Create source app at `apps/tenant-<name>/`
2. Implement sections following TBP (View.tsx, schema.ts, types.ts, index.ts per section)
3. Add `dist` script to source app's `package.json`
4. Create `packages/cli/assets/templates/<name>/manifest.json`
5. Run `npm run dist:dna:all` to generate `src_tenant.sh`
6. Verify with `npm run check:templates`
7. Add template option to CLI in `packages/cli/src/index.js`

## Section capsule structure (TBP)

Each section in a tenant source app follows:

```
src/components/<SectionType>/
  View.tsx      — React component rendering the section
  schema.ts     — JSON schema for inspector editability
  types.ts      — TypeScript types for section data
  index.ts      — re-export barrel
```

## Tenant data structure (JSP)

```
src/data/
  config/
    site.json     — site-wide config (name, logo, colors, SEO)
    menu.json     — navigation structure
    theme.json    — design tokens
  pages/
    home.json     — page definition with sections array
    about.json
    ...
```

## CLI aliases

Both `olonjs` (primary) and `jsonpages` (compatibility) are registered bin commands.
